# What is Computer Vision?


<img src="https://images.code.org/0ec49f831a315a6e3d9df9398d14302f-image-1714587189025.png" alt="Image of AI bot and a model card" style="border-radius:10px; float: right; ; height: 150px; margin: 20px 20px 0px 10px; ">

## Defining Computer Vision:

#### Computer vision is a field of artificial intelligence that enables computers and systems to **derive meaningful information** from digital images, videos, and other visual inputs. 

#### It is commonly seen in everyday applications such as facial recognition, autonomous vehicles, and image processing software.



<br>
<br>

---

## Why Students Should Learn It:

#### Learning computer vision equips students with cutting-edge skills relevant in numerous industries, fostering a blend of technical proficiency and critical thinking. 

#### This knowledge not only prepares them for future careers in technology but also helps them **understand and ethically engage** with the increasingly digital world around them.


